BEIJING, Oct. 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese stocks closed lower on Thursday, with the benchmark Shanghai Composite Index down 1.23 percent to 3,518.42 points. The Shenzhen Component Index closed 1.03 percent lower at 14,244.82 points. The combined turnover of stocks covered by the two indices stood at 1.11 trillion yuan (about 173.2 billion U.S. dollars), up from 1.08 trillion yuan on the previous trading day. Stocks in the pumped-storage hydropower and home appliance sectors led the gains, while those related to gas and oil exploitation and coal were among the biggest losers. The ChiNext Index, tracking China's Nasdaq-style board of growth enterprises, lost 0.92 percent to close at 3,278.36 points on Thursday. Enditem